item.title: Need help with portforwarding
item.dc:creator: @zingerman111 zingerman111
item.description:
@zingerman111 wrote:

just go to your cmd and look at your IPV4 Adress and use that in your ip for portforwarding
most routers let you go to the site 192.168.1.1 others have 192.168.0.1 try one next you
wanna go to your portforwarding/ whatever else it says set your ports to single set your
TCP/UDP to both so it connects no matter what and finally you save setting reset no-ip or hamachi
whichever you using and start your server up your server should work then
